Code Explanation
Key Sections of the Code:
HTML:

Contains <section> elements for each question.
Each section includes question text, options, and a hidden <div> for the star rating.
CSS:

Used for styling questions, options, timer, and stars.
Implements animations like sliding and fading.
JavaScript (jQuery):

Handles dynamic interactions, such as:
Sliding animations for questions.
Countdown timer logic.
Dynamic display of star ratings.
Customization
You can customize the quiz by:

Adding Questions:

Add more <section> elements with appropriate content for new questions in the index.html file.
Adjusting Timer:

Modify the timer duration by changing the timeLeft variable in the script.js file.
Styling:

Change the quiz appearance by editing the style.css file.
